```


:::
:::



The VIFs are really big, so centering age will help the multicolinearity of the model.



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mod2 = lm(y ~ age_c + age_c_sq, data = df)
```
:::



Where `age_c` is age centered at the mean, and `age_c_sq` is the centered age squared.



::: {.cell}

